function_args: "{\"project_name\":\"greet_app\",\"file_path\":\"main.py\",\"content\":\"import tkinter as tk\\nimport logging\\nimport os\\n\\n\\ndef greet():\\n    name = entry.get().strip()\\n    if not name:\\n        msg = \\\"Please enter your name.\\\"\\n    else:\\n        msg = f\\\"Nice to meet you, {name}!\\\"\\n    logging.info(f\\\"User entered name: {name}\\\")\\n    logging.info(f\\\"Greeting displayed: {msg}\\\")\\n    result_label.config(text=msg)\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Setup logging to a file in the project directory\\n    log_file = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), 'greet_app.log')\\n    logging.basicConfig(\\n        level=logging.INFO,\\n        format=\\\"%(asctime)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s\\\",\\n        handlers=[\\n            logging.FileHandler(log_file, mode='a'),\\n            logging.StreamHandler()\\n        ]\\n    )\\n\\n    # Build GUI\\n    root = tk.Tk()\\n    root.title(\\\"Greeting App\\\")\\n\\n    prompt_label = tk.Label(root, text=\\\"Enter your name:\\\")\\n    prompt_label.pack(padx=10, pady=5)\\n\\n    entry = tk.Entry(root)\\n    entry.pack(padx=10, pady=5)\\n\\n    greet_button = tk.Button(root, text=\\\"Greet\\\", command=greet)\\n    greet_button.pack(padx=10, pady=5)\\n\\n    result_label = tk.Label(root, text=\\\"\\\")\\n    result_label.pack(padx=10, pady=5)\\n\\n    root.mainloop()\\n\"}"
